article.headline: Davidson 87, Sewanee 42
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. (AP) -- Jason Morton scored 17 points to lead Davidson in an 87-42 win Friday night against Sewanee. Logan Kosmalski added 13 points and nine rebounds for the Wildcats (5-4). Eugene Talley led the Division III Tigers with 16 points and five rebounds. No other player had more than six points as Sewanee (5-3) made just 16-of-53 (30 percent) of its shots from the floor. Davidson started the game with an 8-0 run and never trailed. They dominated inside, outscoring the Tigers 46-12 in the paint. Matt McKillop hit 4-of-9 3-point tries for 12 points, but the rest of the Wildcats struggled from behind the arc, going a combined 4-for-18.
